The paper presents a model for network formation as a non-cooperative game, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The focus of the paper is on the formation of networks for information gathering, which involves social and cognitive aspects, making it relevant to social and information sciences (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the efficiency of equilibrium networks, which is a topic in social network analysis (cs.SOC). The model presented in the paper involves decision-making by cognitive agents, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the production of information, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
